alone (as well with Moses as with David). The word VIHI, *Vayehi*, "and
it was done," is also alone. (As if the six members were considered
separately, seeing that V, *Vau*, occupieth the first place in the word
VIHI, *Vayehi*.

\[This statement, that the supernal mother symbolized by the word Hoa,
He, seems at first sight at variance with the statement in another
place, that Hoa represents Macroprosopus. But the letter H in the
Tetragrammaton symbolizes the supernal mother, and this is also the
initial letter of Hoa. And again by Gematria (see Introduction) Hoa, HVA
