text itself, showing how the last letter of this form of the
Tetragrammaton, namely, I, *Yod*, may be said to symbolize the bride,
since

<span id="page_57">p. 57</span>

\[paragraph continues\] God himself might behold in that light the path
of conjunctive foundation, which the word "goodness" pointeth out; but
when the foundation is in the act of conjunction--that is, under the
